Definition: serving or tending to provoke, excite, or stimulate
Example: stimulating discussion or exciting controversy; a provocative remark; a provocative smile; provocative Irish tunes which...compel the hearers to dance- Anthony Trollope
Synonyms: verb, emotion, provoke, communication, UNPROVOCATIVE, EXCITING, serving, or, tending, to, excite, stimulate, stimulating, discussion, exciting, controversy, a, provocative, remark, smile, Irish, tunes, which, compel, the, hearers, dance, -, Anthony, Trollope
Category: adj.all
